  <p class="cover-subtitle">Protecting Citizen Data &nbsp;·&nbsp; Governing Digital Infrastructure &nbsp;·&nbsp; Ensuring Continuity of Service Delivery</p>
  <p class="cover-abstract">
    As governments and critical infrastructure operators face accelerating digital transformation, the risks of technological dependency, extraterritorial legal exposure, and loss of sovereign control over data and infrastructure have never been greater. The Digital &amp; Data Sovereignty Assessment Tool (DDSAT) provides a structured, quantitative methodology to evaluate an organisation's sovereignty posture across 14 domains and five pillars, generating a Digital Sovereignty Index and actionable KPIs to guide strategic investment and policy decisions.
