<!-- ── SECTION 7: KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS ─────────────── -->
<section class="wp-section" id="kpis">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Section 07</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</h2>
  </div>

  <p>A central objective of DDSAT is to translate the nuanced findings of a comprehensive maturity assessment into a set of discrete, quantifiable Key Performance Indicators suitable for executive reporting, cross-agency benchmarking, and longitudinal progress tracking. KPIs bridge the gap between the operational detail of individual assessment domains and the strategic visibility that ministers, board members, and senior officials require to make informed investment and policy decisions.</p>
  <p>Each of DDSAT's 12 KPIs is derived directly from domain scores, ensuring full traceability between executive-level metrics and the underlying assessment evidence. KPIs are colour-coded using a traffic-light threshold system: <span class="threshold-g">Green ≥ 80%</span> indicates a managed-to-optimizing posture; <span class="threshold-a">Amber 40–79%</span> indicates a defined-to-developing posture requiring planned investment; and <span class="threshold-r">Red &lt; 40%</span> indicates a critical gap requiring urgent remediation.</p>
  <p>The <strong>Vendor Dependency Risk Index</strong> is intentionally inverted: a higher score indicates greater sovereign risk (more dependency), rather than greater maturity. This ensures that executive audiences receive an unambiguous risk signal in the domain where complacency is most prevalent.</p>

