<section class="wp-section" id="roadmap">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Section 09</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Implementation Roadmap</h2>
  </div>
  <p>DDSAT is designed to be conducted within an eight-week assessment cycle, producing a complete DSI, domain scorecard, KPI dashboard, and prioritised remediation roadmap. The assessment follows four structured phases, with an ongoing cycle of improvement and annual reassessment thereafter.</p>

  <div class="roadmap">
    <div class="roadmap-line"></div>
    <div class="roadmap-phase">
      <div class="phase-dot pd-1">1</div>
      <div class="phase-content">
        <div class="phase-timing">Phase 1 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Weeks 1–2</div>
        <div class="phase-title">Scope &amp; Mobilise</div>
        <ul class="phase-items">
          <li>Define the assessment boundary and any in-scope exclusions (e.g., classified systems)</li>
          <li>Assemble the assessment team: lead assessor, domain subject matter experts, legal counsel, and CISO</li>
          <li>Secure executive sponsorship and formal mandate from the relevant accountable executive</li>
          <li>Brief key stakeholders and establish evidence collection channels</li>
          <li>Agree assessment calendar, review milestones, and governance arrangements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-phase">
      <div class="phase-dot pd-2">2</div>
      <div class="phase-content">
        <div class="phase-timing">Phase 2 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Weeks 3–6</div>
        <div class="phase-title">Conduct Assessment</div>
        <ul class="phase-items">
          <li>Complete all 84 DDSAT questions across 14 domains with relevant SMEs providing domain-specific input</li>
          <li>Gather documentary evidence for each response: policies, audit reports, contracts, test records</li>
          <li>Validate responses through triangulation of multiple evidence sources where available</li>
          <li>Flag contested responses for senior review and document rationale for scoring decisions</li>
          <li>Conduct structured interviews with domain owners to test understanding behind documented policies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-phase">
      <div class="phase-dot pd-3">3</div>
      <div class="phase-content">
        <div class="phase-timing">Phase 3 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Weeks 7–8</div>
        <div class="phase-title">Analyse &amp; Report</div>
        <ul class="phase-items">
          <li>Generate DSI, domain scores, pillar scores, and all 12 KPIs from assessment responses</li>
          <li>Produce radar charts, domain scorecards, and maturity level assessments for executive reporting</li>
          <li>Rank remediation recommendations by severity, strategic impact, and implementation effort</li>
          <li>Prepare executive summary, detailed findings report, and board-level KPI dashboard</li>
          <li>Present findings to the accountable executive and agree priority actions and ownership</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="roadmap-phase">
      <div class="phase-dot pd-4">↻</div>
      <div class="phase-content">
        <div class="phase-timing">Phase 4 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Ongoing</div>
        <div class="phase-title">Remediate &amp; Reassess</div>
        <ul class="phase-items">
          <li>Implement remediation roadmap with domain owners accountable for specific KPI improvements</li>
          <li>Track KPI trends quarterly through the executive oversight and accountability framework</li>
          <li>Conduct interim domain-level reviews where significant changes occur (major procurements, incidents, legislative changes)</li>
          <li>Repeat the full DDSAT assessment annually to generate trend data, track maturity progression, and refresh the remediation roadmap</li>
