<section class="wp-section" id="glossary">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Glossary</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Key Terms &amp; Definitions</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="glossary-grid">
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">Digital Sovereignty</div><div class="glossary-def">The capacity of a state or organisation to exercise autonomous authority over its digital assets, data flows, and technology infrastructure free from undue external control or extraterritorial legal exposure.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">Data Residency</div><div class="glossary-def">The physical or geographic location in which data is stored and processed. Data residency requirements mandate that certain categories of data remain within specified national boundaries.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">Data Localisation</div><div class="glossary-def">Legal or policy requirements mandating that data be collected, processed, and/or stored within a specific jurisdiction, preventing transfer to or processing in other countries.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">Critical National Infrastructure (CNI)</div><div class="glossary-def">The assets, systems, and networks whose incapacitation or destruction would have a debilitating effect on national security, economic security, public health, or public safety.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">CSIRT</div><div class="glossary-def">Computer Security Incident Response Team. A specialist team responsible for receiving, reviewing, and responding to cybersecurity incident reports and activity within a defined constituency.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">SOC</div><div class="glossary-def">Security Operations Centre. A facility housing a team of security analysts who monitor, detect, analyse, and respond to cybersecurity incidents, typically on a 24/7 basis.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">HSM</div><div class="glossary-def">Hardware Security Module. A physical computing device that provides secure key generation, storage, and cryptographic operations, protecting cryptographic keys from disclosure or misuse.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">PKI</div><div class="glossary-def">Public Key Infrastructure. A framework of policies, procedures, hardware, software, and people used to create, manage, distribute, use, store, and revoke digital certificates and manage public-key encryption.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">Zero Trust</div><div class="glossary-def">A security model based on the principle "never trust, always verify" — requiring continuous verification of identity and device trustworthiness for every access request, regardless of network location.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">TIA (Transfer Impact Assessment)</div><div class="glossary-def">An assessment conducted before transferring personal data to a third country to evaluate whether the destination provides an essentially equivalent level of data protection to the originating jurisdiction.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">SCC (Standard Contractual Clauses)</div><div class="glossary-def">Pre-approved contractual terms issued by a data protection authority (notably the European Commission) that provide an approved legal mechanism for transferring personal data to third countries.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">BCR (Binding Corporate Rules)</div><div class="glossary-def">Internal data protection policies used by multinational corporations to transfer personal data internationally within a corporate group, approved by the relevant supervisory authority as providing adequate protection.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">DPIA (Data Protection Impact Assessment)</div><div class="glossary-def">A process designed to describe processing activities, assess their necessity and proportionality, and help manage the risks to individuals arising from the processing of their personal data.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">PAM (Privileged Access Management)</div><div class="glossary-def">A cybersecurity strategy and technology for controlling, monitoring, securing, and auditing all privileged identities and activities across an organisation's IT environment.</div></div>
    <div class="glossary-item"><div class="glossary-term">DSI (Digital Sovereignty Index)</div><div class="glossary-def">The aggregate, weighted composite score generated by DDSAT, expressed on a 0–100 scale, representing an organisation's overall digital sovereignty posture across all five pillars and 14 domains.</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

